weird
file name extension shows porto, then on hub it changes to port
bad mapping somewhere? e.g. `{ "Porto": "port" }`
because also map name on overview is "Port"
well there's a maps table which it uses for lookup, and porto is in there, but it's added port for some reason, dont know why it's trimming the o
that port one was created a few minutes ago when you uploaded again
but still, it's doing a full text comparison, so it should pick porto
wacky
cached somn somewhere?
nah no cache
I think `rtrim` removes all instances of `.` `p` `b` `o`
from the right
http://php.net/manual/en/function.rtrim.php
"returns a string with whitespace (or other characters) stripped from the end"
yeah so all that should be left is ARC_TVT_Escaped_J.Porto
split by .
nope, strips `o.pbo` because `o` is in "character mask" `.pbo` and on the right side
omfg
lol 😉
nice find
glad to help!
alright upload it now

It's literally one line per bit message, and we are supposed to have discussions in mission discussion not archub so why would we move it there?
In Hub V2, notifications that concern an individual (comments, notes, verification) will also be DM'd to that user

My thinking goes that the discussions we have in #deleted-channel tend to involve the content that gets posted as AARs to ARCHUB. I don't think the bot linking to AARs would be at all in the way of any discussions going on there, and would often directly contribute to them.
Also, the other notifications here in #archub seem to be more about notifying admins and mission makers / testers about the status of upcoming missions. I would guess that many users mute this channel for that reason.
There aren't going to be any changes made to the current version of Hub (thus this bot), but in V2 notifications like these are changing quite a bit so I'd wait for that
No worries, just some organizational details to consider, then. Good luck with Hub 2.0!
